The paper deals with the study of maximum numbers of pseudo-triangulations and pointed pseudo-triangulations that can be embedded over a specific set of points in the plane or contained in a specific triangulation. This involves the use of computational geometry techniques and combinatorial algorithms, which are typically covered in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of bounds and complexity, which are relevant to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category, as it involves the analysis of upper and lower bounds for the number of pseudo-triangulations.
